Former Military Head of State, General Yakubu Gowon (rtd) has expressed regret over the failure of successive governments to continue with the National Development Plan of 1975 – 1980. Gowon said this at the presentation of the book, General Domkat Yah Bali (GCON) As Ponzhi Tarok Designate, a contextual analysis of the imbroglio.” The former Head of State said the failure of successive governments to adhere to the beautiful work of the dedicated Nigerian military officers led by General Damkat Bali denied Nigeria the benefit of coordinated development for a great nation. His words: “If only the development plan that we had at that time, 1975 – 1980. If it was continued, if they had carried it through, it would have made all the difference,” General Gowon stated. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state… Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report.… ORITAMEFA BAPTIST MODEL SCHOOLS, (OBMS), IBADAN 
